gurmukhi: ਗਜਾ ਜੂਹ ਗੱਜੇ || ਸੁਭੰ ਸੰਜ ਸੱਜੇ ||੧੬||
transliteration: Gadaa Jooh Gadje|| Soubhan Sanj Sajje||16||
translation: The elephants began to roar in groups and bedecked with armour, the warriors seemed impressive.16.

gurmukhi: ਚਹੂੰ ਓਰ ਢੂਕੇ || ਗਜੰ ਜੂਹ ਝੂਕੇ ||
transliteration: Chahoon Or Dhooke|| Gadan Jooh Jhooke||
translation: Gathering from all the four sides, the groups of elephants began a fight.

gurmukhi: ਸਰੰ ਬਯੂਹ ਛੂਟੇ || ਰਿਪੰ ਸੀਸ ਫੂਟੇ ||੧੭||
transliteration: Saran Byooh Chhodhte|| Ripan Sees Phoote||17||
translation: The volleys of arrows were shot and the heads of the kings were shattered. 17.

gurmukhi: ੳੁਠੇ ਨਾਦ ਭਾਰੀ || ਰਿਸੇ ਛੱਤ੍ਰ ਧਾਰੀ ||
transliteration: Outhe Naad Bhdaree|| Rise Chhattra Dhdaree||
translation: The frightful sound emanated and all the kings got infuriated.

gurmukhi: ਘਿਰਯੋ ਰਾਮ ਸੈਨੰ || ਸਿਵੰ ਜੇਮ ਮੈਨੰ ||੧੮||
transliteration: Ghiryo Raam Sainan|| Sivan Jem Mainan||18||
translation: Parashurama was besieged by the army like Shiva encircled by the forces of Cupid.18.

gurmukhi: ਰਣੰ ਰੰਗ ਰੱਤੇ || ਤ੍ਰਸੇ ਤੇਜ ਤੱਤੇ ||
transliteration: Ranan Ran Ratte|| Trase Tej Tatte||
translation: All being absorbed and dyed with the dye of war, feared the glory of others.

gurmukhi: ੳੁਠੀ ਸੈਣ ਧੂਰੰ || ਰਹਯੋ ਗੈਣ ਪੂਰੰ ||੧੯||
translation: So much dust arose by (the movement of the) army that the sky was filled with dust.19.

gurmukhi: ਘਣੇ ਢੋਲ ਬੱਜੇ || ਮਹਾਂ ਬੀਰ ਗੱਜੇ ||
transliteration: Ghane Dhol Bajje|| Mahaan Beer Gadje||
translation: The drums resounded violently and the mighty warriors began to roar.

transliteration: Mano Singh Chhoutte|| Iman Beer Joutte||20||
translation: The warriors were fighting each other like the freely roaming lions.20.
